://imgur.com/gallery/wu7qEPd</link><description><![CDATA[<div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/GXcA6Kv.png" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div></div>]]></description><guid>https://imgur.com/a/wu7qEPd</guid><dc:creator><![CDATA[randomthingsonthenet]]></dc:creator></item><item><title>I can almost hear the howling monkeys and their infernal screeching now</title><link>https://imgur.com/gallery/rqCI8hL</link><description><![CDATA[<div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/PRR0HmQ.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>https://bsky.app/profile/timhannan.bsky.social/post/3lxkbiuq3622f</div></div>]]></description><guid>https://imgur.com/a/rqCI8hL</guid><dc:creator><![CDATA[malbec]]></dc:creator></item><item><title>He's no doggo, but he's the goodest boy.</title><link>https://imgur.com/gallery/Qj6Q3SH</link><description><![CDATA[<div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/uMTJIXz.gif" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div></div>]]></description><guid>https://imgur.com/a/Qj6Q3SH</guid><dc:creator><![CDATA[ElbowDeepInAHorse]]></dc:creator></item><item><title>Imgur blackout FYBD</title><link>https://imgur.com/gallery/4BC9d1o</link><description><![CDATA[<div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/8Xth5Tn.png" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div></div>]]></description><guid>https://imgur.com/a/4BC9d1o</guid><dc:creator><![CDATA[FarmerTed]]></dc:creator></item><item><title>Feel Good Inc</title><link>https://imgur.com/gallery/WxKJMxO</link><description><![CDATA[<div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/UAoGsLY.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>Loki, (Supernatural, before we knew he was Gabriel, not Hiddleston, sorry Tom) just had a tumor removed from behind his left eye. Ohio State University Veterinary did one HELL of a job! Pricey? Yes. Bitching? No. Don't worry, it gets better!
(Notice his left ear! One of the newer students learned a valuable lesson about razors and cat ear twitches! Don't worry, he's fine, and we forgive her. It IS a learning hospital, and she helped with a win that would have been impossible 10 years ago!)
EDIT: We're already thinking about getting him an ear cuff, or maybe clip one for his other ear. (He does NOT eat yummy things, like the little Bella that fall off of his toys!)</div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/LfT3hMD.gif" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>In three short months, we've been to three different Vets, 4 if you include Neuro. First vet (lower case intentional) were new owners of previous care. Lost his records twice. Asked if he wanted his flea meds. He's strictly indoor, but we live in the sticks. Things went downhill FAST. Loki started wandering the house aimlessly, and would stop in corners or at walls like a Roomba that's forgotten what to do when it's supposed to turn. He would walk gingerly on his feet as if they were in pain, hindsight telling us he was unsure of his environment and having vision trouble.</div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/WeQXx7M.gif" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>Waited longer than we should to take him to OSU, but we wanted to believe his vet that he was just getting old. After 2 weeks, we took him back, the situation worsening every day. As stated, they couldn't't find his records for a second time. We found out that the "new and improved meds" had side effects for cats with Neuro trouble. My wife and I had never seen a reason to believe he had any disorder, but our faith has been shaken, and rightfully so. Our cat had PROBLEMS at this point and the fear started. Screw the money, OSU trains most of the Vets in Ohio, so we'll go there. Three trips, an MRI, and one pissed off cat later, we had confirmation. Loki had a tumor behind his left eye. The Doc was completely honest about probabilities and such, the numbers were even HOPEFUL.</div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/foyw982.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>Now I will not ask for money. I am blessed with a strong back, and a job that allows my ALMOST all the overtime I can work. My manager is fairly awesome. I am NOT in this equation. In the vids above, the Docs explaining the money costs, and as you can see, we couldn't care less. When Loki came out of surgery, they had trouble walking him up. By day 2, they were plenty worried. I was not. That's MY cat. We're not what you would call "well socialized". Imagine. You have a pain in your head ALL the time for months, haven't been eating it drinking well, can't see, suddenly you're in a strange place, with strange animals, NOTHING is familiar. A LOT more noise than you're used to. You would probably stress sleep as well.</div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/eKBLe9U.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>The moment my wife and I walked in front of him, his head popped up, he was "Looking" for us, clearly, but clearly could not see. Nevertheless, he started reaching out, trying his best to get up and get to us while cathed and hooked up to monitors, relieving the worst fears of the Doc. When my wife turned my back to speak with Doc, my little gremlin let out the tiniest cries and started FIGHTING to get to her. 
 Yesterday we were encouraged to bring his favorite foods to see if he'd respond better. (He's a picky damn eater) We opened a pouch of tuna,(I know it can be bad in excess, we try to limit it), and you would have thought somebody fed him after midnight. Three weeks ago. Doc was skeptical, but saw me mincing it so it was suitable for a post op tummy. The half I wouldn't let him eat was saved by the Doc for leverage when Loki gets.. Difficult when the testing needs done. My fur baby has NEVER been a trained monkey, he does what HE wants.</div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/fEMeeVp.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>We're hoping to bring him home tomorrow, and we thank you for ALL your kind wishes! With the world being what it is, the breaking of Imgur, we REALLY needed this Win. I've loved this community for a decade, even if I was a lurker, and wish you all HALF of what I'm feeling right now! Don't be sarcastic, I'm f-ing Leo on the bow!</div></div>]]></description><guid>https://imgur.com/a/WxKJMxO</guid><dc:creator><![CDATA[yousersubzero13]]></dc:creator></item><item><title>FYBD</title><link>https://imgur.com/gallery/QwRn3Nz</link><description><![CDATA[<div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/YfEiQM3.png" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div></div>]]></description><guid>https://imgur.com/a/QwRn3Nz</guid><dc:creator><![CDATA[arikelrecords2000]]></dc:creator></item><item><title>theme</title><link>https://imgur.com/gallery/f5FE0KB</link><description><![CDATA[<div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/hfQmid6.png" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div></div>]]></description><guid>https://imgur.com/a/f5FE0KB</guid><dc:creator><![CDATA[Niobe68]]></dc:creator></item><item><title>Now is the time my first post!</title><link>https://imgur.com/gallery/uMArSlI</link><description><![CDATA[<div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/xhVIdui.png" style="max-width: 90%;